    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup today is anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (80.03) and **Andy Pages** (69.83), both of whom benefit significantly from a favorable matchup against Chris Paddack. **Kyle Tucker** is our premier play, leveraging a high base projection bolstered by a 15% SP skill advantage and a wind-out scenario at the park, making him the cornerstone of our offensive strategy. **Andy Pages** follows close behind; despite a neutral platoon, his ability to capitalize on Paddack\u2019s high xERA and the wind assistance justifies his high placement in the order. Elsewhere, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (65.71) remains a high-floor selection against Ranger Suarez, buoyed by a strong xwOBA profile that continues to drive his efficiency rating well into the \"Strong\" start tier.\n\nThe most difficult decision for today\u2019s card was leaving **Nolan Schanuel** (52.03) on the bench. While his score is technically superior to that of **Josh Lowe** (47.74) and **Liam Hicks** (42.45), the optimizer favored the specific situational utility of the starters\u2014particularly **Josh Lowe\u2019s** ability to leverage the opponent's slow delivery despite the wind-in risk. **Miguel Vargas** (53.92) also narrowly cleared the cut, though his score suffered a notable 9% haircut due to unfavorable wind conditions. Managers should monitor the \"Lineup Pending\" status for all starters; specifically, **Liam Hicks** faces a stiff test against Yoshinobu Yamamoto, and while his platoon advantage provides a boost, the elite nature of the opposing pitcher makes this a high-risk, low-reward start if the batting order turns out less favorable than our current #5 assumption.",
